<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="203" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1614,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1614,1640]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This new species differs from all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1837" box="[720,799,1614,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[720,799,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Lyroda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following character combination: anterior margin of clypeus with two sets of three teeth laterally, two teeth medially and two sets of two intermediate teeth, median set of clypeal teeth narrow and cuspidate (
<figureCitation box="[627,698,1686,1713]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Figs 3</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[735,767,1686,1713]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–64" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,189,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 58–64. Anterior clypeal margins: 58. Lyroda aurea sp. nov. holotype ♀; 59. Lyroda nuda sp. nov. holotype ♀; 60. Lyroda salai Giner Marí. ♀; 61. Lyroda binghami Tsuneki. ♀; 62. Lyroda binghami Tsuneki. ♂; 63. Lyroda formosa (Smith). ♀; 64. Lyroda formosa (Smith). ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141505/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">58</figureCitation>
). Forewing with infumation crossing two submarginal cells and apex of second discoidal cell (
<figureCitation box="[531,599,1722,1749]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Dense golden setae on clypeus, frons, pronotum, scutum, lateral margines of scutellum, metanotum and all sides of propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[756,858,1758,1785]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Figs 1–4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="205" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1614,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1794,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[355,459,1794,1820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[469,490,1795,1821]" pageId="2" pageNumber="203" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[509,578,1794,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[605,666,1794,1820]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Head</emphasis>
. Head broader than long; HW1.25–1.30 × HL; IODc 1.25–1.92 × IODv; POD 1.08–1.25 × OOD; inner eye orbits at vertex parallel; vertex and frons densely punctate, PIS on average ≥ PD; median furrow distinctly dividing frons into two portions (
<figureCitation box="[942,1012,1866,1893]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); clypeus punctate, PIS on average ≤ PD; anterior margin of clypeus usually with two cuspidate teeth medially and two sets of three prominent teeth at lateral margins, with two sets of two intermediate teeth (
<figureCitation box="[781,851,1938,1965]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">Figs 3</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[887,918,1938,1965]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–64" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[181,1400,189,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[178,1409,181,1918]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 58–64. Anterior clypeal margins: 58. Lyroda aurea sp. nov. holotype ♀; 59. Lyroda nuda sp. nov. holotype ♀; 60. Lyroda salai Giner Marí. ♀; 61. Lyroda binghami Tsuneki. ♀; 62. Lyroda binghami Tsuneki. ♂; 63. Lyroda formosa (Smith). ♀; 64. Lyroda formosa (Smith). ♂." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141505/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="203">58</figureCitation>
); mandible deeply cut near base to give rise to two tooth like prominences, distinctly incised at base on outer margin; antenna thin, scape as long as F2, F1 slightly longer (1.32–1.35 ×) than F2, F1 3.52–3.96 × its apical width.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" startId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1943,2040]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,309,1943,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">FIGURES 1–9</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar" authorityName="Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar" authorityYear="2021" box="[321,737,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lyroda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[321,457,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">Lyroda aurea</emphasis>
Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[744,824,1944,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[744,824,1944,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="204" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis box="[199,280,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotal collar lower than scutum, with three prominent tubercles; anterior third of scutum with two medial parallel carinae diverging posteriorly; scutum with medial longitudinal depression; propleuron with oblique furrow, mesopleuron convex; scutum, scutellum and metanotum with fine dense punctures, PIS, on average, less than PD (
<figureCitation box="[255,323,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); forewing with infumation crossing two submarginal cells and apex of second discoidal cell (
<figureCitation box="[1360,1423,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig.7</figureCitation>
); hind tibiae with 7-9 spines on posterior external margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis box="[199,336,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Propodeum.</emphasis>
Dorsum with median carina extending close to posterior margin where short transverse carinae are present, surface rugoso-reticulate (
<figureCitation box="[536,603,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), without lateral carina; side shiny with minute punctures, inconspicuously alutaceous, PIS on average greater than PD (
<figureCitation box="[650,718,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); posterior surface with narrow, wedge shaped deep median furrow, sides of furrow with somewhat sinuate rugae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis box="[199,275,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Gaster</emphasis>
. Basal platform of first segment approximately triangular with constriction, having distinct edges; Gt1 width 1.03–1.07 × its length (
<figureCitation box="[490,559,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); gaster micropunctate with microscopic setae, surface alutaceous and shiny; pygidial plate with lateral carinae as in 
<figureCitation box="[592,660,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis box="[199,296,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Vestiture</emphasis>
. Setae golden; dense on clypeus, base of mandible, antenna, gena, frons, vertex behind eye, tibiae, femora, posterior and posterolateral area of scutum, lateral margins of scutellum and metanotum, all sides of propodeum, and sternal areas of thorax (
<figureCitation box="[538,690,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Figs 1, 2 &amp; 4</figureCitation>
); discontinuous golden band of pile on Gt2–Gt3, setae extensively distributed on Gt1, more densely distributed at apex, forming band of pile (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1089,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); body extensively pilose, pygidium with dense, stiff brown setae mixed with longer erect brown bristles (
<figureCitation box="[1014,1082,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis box="[199,336,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Colouration</emphasis>
. Black; mandible, tibial spurs and tarsal claws more or less ferruginous; wings hyaline, slightly infumated at two external submarginal cells and at apex of second discoidal cell, veins testaceous, stigma, subcostal and radial cell blackish brown (
<figureCitation box="[504,572,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[183,1403,190,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[172,1415,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–9. Lyroda aurea Mawadda &amp; Girish Kumar sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view; 2. Head, frontal view; 3. Lower half of head, frontal view; 4. Head &amp; thorax; 5. Propodeum, dorsal view; 6. Propodeum, lateral view; 7. Forewing; 8. Gaster, dorsal view; 9. Pygidium." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141487/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">
<emphasis box="[199,311,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Variation.</emphasis>
Anterior clypeal margin usually with two intermediate sets of two teeth each. Sometimes, however, only one intermediate tooth is present on one side compared to two intermediate teeth on the other side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" box="[199,419,943,969]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">BL. 7.91–8.00 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,1725]" box="[199,389,979,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="205">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
